This paper discusses the security and performance of certificateless two-party authenticated key agreement (CTAKA) protocols, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on improving the performance of CTAKA protocols without using bilinear pairings, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the security of the proposed protocol under the random oracle model, which may also place it under the sub-categories of cyber security (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
